As Scary Wombat said, you are comparing a `String` to an `int`. There are two Solutions to this:

1. Compare to a `String` instead of an `int` (Note that you have to use `equals` here instead of `==`)

```
if(option.equals(&quot;1&quot;)) {
    //...
} else if (option.equals(&quot;2&quot;)) {
    //...
}
```

2. Assuming `input` is of type `Scanner`, read an `int` instead of a `String` (Note that this will throw an Exception if the user Inputs something that is not an integer)
```
option = input.nextInt();
```

